{"article_id":"A2AHk5AFtKEDfoIl","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A terror attack in Boston was followed by a massive manhunt for bombers Dzhokhar A. Tsarnaev and his brother Tamerlan .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"On the international stage , the father of the Boston Marathon bombers , Anzor Tsrnaev , spoke from the Russian city of Makhachkala .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"Mr. Tsrnaev said","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"\" all hell would break loose \"","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"if his 19-year-old son was killed by authorities .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"Here ' s a recap , or wrap , on the week","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"that was from","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"The :","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"- Police capture Marathon Bombing suspect Dzhokhar Tsarnaev in Watertown","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"Police have finally bagged the second Boston Marathon bombing suspect Friday night .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"In a dramatic end to the daylong manhunt , 19-year-old suspect Dzhokhar Tsarnaev was captured alive","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"after police zeroed in on his hideout inside a boat","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"stored for the winter in a Watertown , Mass. , backyard .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"- Boston ' bombers are brothers ' from Chechnya ;","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"police name both","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"The two suspects","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"involved in Monday ' s marathon bombings in Boston","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"were brothers","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"and hailed from overseas ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"various media reported Friday .","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Fox News said","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Suspect No . 2","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"who wore the white hat at the Boston Marathon bombings","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"has been identified as Dzhokhar A. Tsarnaev , 19 .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"He hails from Chechnya","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"and had been in the United States for a little more than a year ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Bill Hemmer from Fox News reported .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"- Senate shoots down background checks for guns ,","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"angers Obama","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"Senators dealt a devastating blow to gun control efforts Wednesday ,","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"defeating the background check compromise","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that was the centerpiece of President Obama ' s post-Newtown push for stiffer laws","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"and leaving advocates struggling to figure out what to do now .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"President Obama angrily blamed the defeat Wednesday of his centerpiece gun-control proposal on lies","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"spread by the National Rifle Association ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"calling it \" a pretty shameful day for Washington . \"","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"\" The gun lobby and its allies willfully lied about the bill , \"","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Mr. Obama said in the White House rose garden about 90 minutes after the vote .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"\" It came down to politics . \"","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"- WOLF :","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"The 1-percenter","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"who doesn ' t pay his ' fair share '","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"- President Obama Resolved :","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"No American citizen shall be required to pay federal income taxes at a rate higher","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"than the country ' s millionaire president pays .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Let ' s call it the Alternative Maximum Fairness Tax :","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Calculate your current tax rate ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"compare it to the president ' s","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"and pay the lower of the two .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"Two bombs explode near the finish line of the Boston Marathon ,","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"killing three","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"and injuring more than 100 .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"Boston bombing suspect Dzhohar Tsarnaev said on his Russian social media page","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"that his world view was \" Islam , \"","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"while his older brother Tamerlan Tsarnaev talked about being \" very religious \"","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"and complained","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"there \" are no values anymore , \"","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"according to an English-language Russian newspaper .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"- Al Qaeda magazine on pressure cookers :","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"' Make a bomb in the kitchen of your mom '","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"CAIRO -","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Homemade bombs","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"built from pressure cookers ,","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"a version of which was used in the Boston Marathon bombings ,","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"have been a frequent weapon of militants in Afghanistan , India and Pakistan .","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Al-Qaeda ' s branch in Yemen once published an online manual","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"on how to make one ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"urging \" lone jihadis \" to act on their own","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"to carry out attacks .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"- Texas fertilizer plant blast ' like a war zone ' ;","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"more than 160 hurt ,","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"some fatally","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"Police on Thursday were still searching for survivors of a devastating Waco , Texas , fertilizer plant explosion","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"that killed up to 15","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"and injured at least 160 .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"Waco Police DepartmentSgt . William Patrick Swanton told Fox News early Thursday morning","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"that the death count is still unknown","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"and could range between 5 and 15 ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"The number of injured is upwards of 160 ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"based on reports from three hospitals","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"that have passed along injury updates to police .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"- Sen. Max Baucus :","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"Health law heading for ' train wreck '","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"A senior Democratic senator","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"who helped write President Obama ' s health care law","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"stunned administration officials","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"by saying openly","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"he thinks","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"it ' s headed for a \" train wreck . \"","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"Sen. Max Baucus of Montana , chairman of the Senate Finance Committee , delivered his tough-love assessment of efforts","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"to implement the Affordable Care Act","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"during a budget hearing","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"that featured Health and Human Services Secretary Kathleen Sebelius .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"- FBI arrests Mississippi man in ricin-tainted mailings to Obama , senator","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"The FBI said late Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"that it had arrested a Mississippi man","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"accused of sending letters","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"tested positive for the poison ricin to President Obama , a U.S. senator and a Mississippi justice official .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"The arrest capped a day","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"in which official Washington was on edge","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"after several senators reported questionable mail","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"delivered to their offices at the Capitol and in their respective states .","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":203,"left":106,"right":202,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":106,"left":0,"right":105,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":105,"left":1,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":2,"right":103,"r